		<div id="post_message_1370491">This is part of the puzzle for players at max level.  The other stuff they have had is pretty standard: raiding/upgrades, factioning, crafting, farming gold, questing (epic book quests), PvPing.  They are raising the cap, so the current maxed players will have a bit to do on release of Moria.<br />
<br />
The thing with this is that it adds oodles of stuff to do, with a measureable outcome.  The Legendaries have 50 levels, nine max legacies, three types of legacy quality (bronze, silver, gold) and can have three relics embedded.  None of it is permanent, all can be switched around for a price.  It means a casual player can participate as far as they can, and a hardcore player can really put a bunch of time and effort (and raiding) into maxing out if they want to do that.</div>
