I enjoyed LOTRO but I just can't bring myself into the game to do quests and such for hours on end that give me absolutely no rewards (other than some silver for selling the quest reward).<br />
<br />
Remember in EQ if you got a chest piece of a raid event? If you weren't raiding areas which were a few expansions old, the raid items always were upgrades. In LOTRO all upgrades are very small.<br />
<br />
Hence, I am not playing until I can progress my character. Preferably where the exp for doing quests isn't wasted as well.<br />
<br />
I just feel that the combination of <br />
- Virtue system that makes you do all newbie areas on all characters<br />
- Complete lack of progression after 50<br />
- Little to no upgrades from crafted gear other than raid stuff<br />
---- Getting light blue crafted gear is trivial. <br />
makes the game go from fun, to bleh upon dinging 50. In other games, you race to the end and there might be little to do. In Lotro there is lots to do at 50, but just little point in doing any of it.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
