		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1370965">My wife and I are the opposite of min-maxers (this is the first MMO she's reached max level in) and we're running out of reasons to log in.  Friendships, deeds and alts are the last three reasons.<br />
<br />
These games are a genre pivoted on progress and stop being interesting when progress stops.  Droigan seems to have brought up this point now because this is the first thread on this game in a while, but it's still valid.  A game needs progression to stay fun and the games that don't provide it will fail.  Hopefully, legendary weapons and 10 levels will increase progression for quite a while.  Maybe the legendary system can be expanded to all armor and that would extend progression out for quite a while.  But a game can't expect success with an &quot;is what it is&quot; attitude.  They need to adapt to player feedback and give people things to be excited about, and poor endgame itemization is hurting this game.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		

		

		

