		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1371022">No its a fine point, I just would have liked to know what he thought about the topic.  He seems focused on getting more levels but really didn't mention the legendary items.<br />
 <br />
I don't think a case could be made that this game has an &quot;it is what it is&quot; attitude with all the content/story updates and changes that have been made to it over time.  Also, i think they are adapting to player feedback - to a point where it doesn't make the game into a McSame.<br />
 <br />
As to itemization, the thing is that there is a huge variety of options.  There just aren't those &quot;killer weapon&quot; choices where you get something overpowered.  The philoosophy is very much one of subtle tradeoffs in stats and builds rather than a &quot;you have to have this weapon because its the best.&quot;  People argue on the boards about which weapon is best, there isn't really a clear choice in many cases.  This is healthy for a game and healthy for its playerbase.  <br />
 <br />
Most people that complain about itemization seem to be wanting to alter a big part of the design concept of this game.  But I would like to hear your thoughts about how you want the itemization carrot to work.  <br />
 <br />
As to excitement, meh.  Its in the eye of the player.  Alot of people lose interest, come back, lose interest, come back.  Lifetime subs was a great idea for this game.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
