			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Re: Legendary items</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#D1D1E1; background-color:#D1D1E1" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		

		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1371169">I really appreciate the massive amounts of content they have provided in the game.  It's a very large and story rich games.  The quest lines are dramatic and well written and are my favorite part of this game.<br />
<br />
My beef all comes down to rewards and &quot;what else can I do?&quot;  The system with every different master crafted item requiring a different component from different rare mobs was broken, but the system where every rare mob drops the same shard, which can be used to make <i>anything</i> is trivial and boring.  Legendary items should fix this for primary items.  What about the rest of our armor?<br />
<br />
I have one last itemization beef and one progression beef.  Why can't something nice randomly drop?  I LOVE master chests in EQ2.  Right now in some rare places like Sarnur, you have an extremely rare chance of getting a teal drop.  They're removing this chance in book 14.  Why?  Not like these items were flooding the market.<br />
<br />
And my last progression beef is with skills.  You buy your skill from a trainer then that's it.  A few skills are trivially quested, but they did a great job with Legendary Traits.  I think I just want more Legendary Trait options and quests to do.  I really liked being conscious of skills/spells needing to be upgraded, but that's all done.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		

		

		

	</td>
